<p>The K. R. Shah
Foundation was incorporated in May 2007 by Chetan Shah to help
individuals in need of financial support for their education and health
care needs. Chetan has a graduate degree in Computer Science and has
been an active Hospice volunteer since 2004. K. R. Shah Foundation
reflects Chetan's passion for community service and his commitment to
promote education and better health care. Currently the foundation
offers $500 grant to students and hospice patients. Over next five
years the foundation will increase number of grants and grant amount</p>
<p><br />
<h3>Mission<br/></h3>
<p>K. R. Shah Foundation is a non profit organization. It seeks to :</p>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Provide education
opportunities to financially challenged candidates.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Provide health care
opportunities to financially challenged patients.</li>
</ul>
</ul>

<h3>Goals</h3>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Help full time college students by providing financial support towards their tuition expenses.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Help hospice patients by providing financial support for their health care needs.</li>
</ul>
</ul>

<h3>Objectives</h3><ul>
<ul>
<li>Provide US$500 fellowship to a student every year</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Provide US$500 financial grant to a hospice patient every year</li>
</ul>
</ul>
